### Upload source maps for SvelteKit error tracking

Source: https://github.com/posthog/posthog.com/blob/master/contents/docs/error-tracking/installation/svelte.mdx

This snippet outlines the process for uploading source maps, which is crucial for de-obfuscating JavaScript errors in PostHog. This step ensures that stack traces are readable and accurately point to the source code, enhancing the debugging experience. The specific command or configuration depends on the tool used for building your SvelteKit project.

```bash
